  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "This PRRO 200152  aims to provide safety net for 1.2 million food-insecure populations in the Mid/Far West Hill and Mountain Regions of Nepal as well as improve nutritional status among vulnerable children aged 5-69 months.   The operation adopts a food and/or cash-for-assets modality, providing rice and pulses and-or cash to beneficiaries working on building critical community assets, enhancing agricultural productivity and adopting alternative livelihood means."
    },
